    "extras": [
      "Indian passport holders can use Indonesia's e-VOA; budget about ₹2,940 and apply online before landing to skip airport queues.",
      "April–June and August–October are the easiest windows for this route; Bali/Java are wettest in December–February.",
      "Exchange INR to USD in India first, then convert to IDR locally for better rates; UPI is not widely usable in Indonesia.",
      "Carry temple-friendly clothing in Bali and Yogyakarta, and watch for canang sari offerings on the ground in Bali.",
      "Pre-book Komodo shared boats in high season because Labuan Bajo departures fill quickly from July to September.",
      "Raja Ampat and Gili days are weather-dependent, so keep one flex half-day if snorkeling visibility matters to you."
    ],
